From Joseph Buehler Subject Re The Bible on the Immaculate COnception In article M JEK writes I will put enmity between you the Serpent and the woman and between your seed and her seed she can also be read he shall crush your head and you shall bruise her or his Genesis In the Hebrew of Genesis the gender is clearly HE shall crush your head and you shall bruise HIS The Latin has feminine forms only by an accident of I have yet to see an adequate explanation of Jerome's translation of Genesis His Latin clearly uses the feminine but I don't know why since the Hebrew is clearly If anyone knows of a scholarly treatment of this puzzle I would appreciate hearing from